{
  "texts": [
    "By leveraging pre-trained weights and extensive data augmentation the model surpasses traditional image processing approaches.",
    "The study demonstrates the model's robustness in handling challenging low-contrast conditions, which is crucial for real-world environmental monitoring.",
    "However, the model struggles with densely packed or overlapping particles, limiting its precision in such scenarios.",
    "Classification of vertebrate specimens using DL is a relatively well-explored task in this realm (refer to Table 7).",
    "Hou et al. (2020) present the ADMorph dataset, a compilation of 3D models of scales from 410 million year old fish, and explore a novel classification approach using a hybrid of DNNs and SVMs."
  ]
}